init_text: When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the "Lost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The catch: it only grows in a remote rain forest.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You want to do it, too.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The team travels for weeks and many are lost to disease, animal attacks, and the elements.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The leader, the botanist, and you.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If you find the plant, will you be able to get home?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: the botanist says, "before we harvest it all."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He mixes the contents in a test tube with water, and begins to shake it.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: In an instant, he begins to age rapidly.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The leader runs to the botanist, who now looks like a frail, old man.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The botanist pulls the leader's face close to his and says, "I'm sorry.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Suddenly, the botanist begins to cough up blood.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The leader, now in a state of panic, runs to the nearest tree.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He climbs it, and surveys the surrounding area.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: a small, purple plant grows from the ground.
